item.description:
Multiple vulnerabilities in Cisco Unity Connection could allow an authenticated, remote attacker&nbsp;to download arbitrary files from an affected system. To exploit these vulnerabilities, the attacker must have valid administrative credentials.&nbsp;
These vulnerabilities are due to improper sanitization of user input to the web-based management interface. An attacker could exploit these vulnerabilities by sending a crafted HTTPS request. A successful exploit could allow the attacker to download arbitrary files from an affected system.
Score: 6.5 (MEDIUM) Vector: CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N

